This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and semantic analysis of Twitter posts. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves analyzing social media data. It could also be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it involves analyzing the stylistic features of tweets. Furthermore, it may belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with detecting fake news, which is a security concern. Finally, it could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves extracting relevant information from Twitter timelines.
